00:09:23,350 --> 00:09:24,516
She's working for Louis.

250
00:09:24,568 --> 00:09:26,351
Litt?
What the hell happened?

251
00:09:26,403 --> 00:09:27,403
Nothing happened.

252
00:09:27,404 --> 00:09:28,854
Just time for a change.

253
00:09:28,856 --> 00:09:30,906
Ah.

254
00:09:30,941 --> 00:09:33,061
If she's working for that
asshole, something happened.

255
00:09:33,077 --> 00:09:35,060
Teddy, you say you know
when it's time to move on,

256
00:09:35,095 --> 00:09:38,530
it's time to move on
from this topic right now.

257
00:09:38,532 --> 00:09:41,199
Okay, Harvey.

258
00:09:41,201 --> 00:09:45,370
All I'm saying is Mrs. Keebler
out there ain't no Donna.

259
00:09:53,213 --> 00:09:54,763
Twice in two days?

260
00:09:54,798 --> 00:09:56,265
People are gonna get
the wrong idea.

261
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,716
Well, they can think what
they're gonna think,

262
00:09:57,768 --> 00:09:59,551
but it's not going to stop me
from giving my boy

263
00:09:59,603 --> 00:10:01,603
an engagement gift.

264
00:10:01,639 --> 00:10:03,522
- You're giving me a case?
- It's not just any case.

265
00:10:03,557 --> 00:10:06,024
This is right up your alley.
Do-gooder lane.

266
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,809
- All right.
- Listen, Mike.

267
00:10:07,861 --> 00:10:09,645
These people got the shaft
for one reason.

268
00:10:09,697 --> 00:10:11,897
They're poor, and no one
gives a shit about 'em.

269
00:10:11,949 --> 00:10:14,466
They need a hero,
and you're that guy.

270
00:10:14,501 --> 00:10:15,567
Why aren't you that guy?

271
00:10:15,619 --> 00:10:17,235
Oh, I am that guy,

272
00:10:17,288 --> 00:10:19,571
but you're the one
getting married to Rachel Zane.

273
00:10:19,573 --> 00:10:21,907
The same Rachel Zane
that I almost got fired,

274
00:10:21,959 --> 00:10:24,409
and then you gave me
a second chance.

275
00:10:24,461 --> 00:10:26,244
So this is your way
of making it up to me?

276
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,546
Listen, Mike,
talk to the plaintiffs,

277
00:10:27,581 --> 00:10:29,414
listen to their stories,
and I promise you

278
00:10:29,466 --> 00:10:31,466
it'll break
your little bleeding heart.

279
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:33,970
Thank you, Jimmy.

280
00:10:33,971 --> 00:10:35,420
Yeah, you bet.

281
00:10:35,472 --> 00:10:37,839
What if I can't get
Jessica to sign off?

282
00:10:37,891 --> 00:10:39,591
Then I'll just
take the case back

283
00:10:39,593 --> 00:10:41,677
and get you a decanter
or some shit.

284
00:10:43,814 --> 00:10:45,180
So it's unanimous.

285
00:10:45,232 --> 00:10:46,848
From now on,
all first-years are required

286
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,601
to bill 2,800 hours
and bring their own lunches.

287
00:10:49,603 --> 00:10:51,653
Congratulations, Louis,
another generation

288
00:10:51,689 --> 00:10:53,822
of associates
smacked into submission.

289
00:10:53,857 --> 00:10:55,657
Now, if you'll excuse me,

290
00:10:55,693 --> 00:10:57,159
I think I'm done
with this meeting.

291
00:10:57,194 --> 00:10:58,493
Harvey, please,
we still have new business.

292
00:10:58,529 --> 00:11:00,112
Speaking of which,
I'd like to propose a change

293
00:11:00,114 --> 00:11:02,614
to the current
compensation formula.

294
00:11:02,616 --> 00:11:03,949
Excuse me?

295
00:11:03,951 --> 00:11:05,500
Well, since taking over
the committee,

296
00:11:05,536 --> 00:11:07,452
I've been evaluating
pay structures,

297
00:11:07,504 --> 00:11:09,588
and I think it's high time
that this firm

298
00:11:09,623 --> 00:11:11,957
put a larger emphasis
on billable hours.

299
00:11:12,009 --> 00:11:14,626
Why don't you stick
to the 48th floor, Jack?

300
00:11:14,628 --> 00:11:16,962
I take it you have a problem
with my proposal.

301
00:11:17,014 --> 00:11:18,263
You're damn right I do.

302
00:11:18,298 --> 00:11:20,182
I just took on the sale
of a man's company,

303
00:11:20,217 --> 00:11:22,601
and my entire fee
is contingent-based.

304
00:11:22,636 --> 00:11:24,469
Because you operate
as your own entity,

305
00:11:24,521 --> 00:11:27,556
while the rest of us are members
of a team known as this firm.

306
00:11:27,608 --> 00:11:28,890
No, because I bring in

307
00:11:28,942 --> 00:11:30,442
a truckload of money
for this firm.

308
00:11:30,477 --> 00:11:32,944
Well, like I said, special rules
for Harvey Specter.

309
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:33,945
You know what, Jack?
That's enough.

310
00:11:33,981 --> 00:11:35,864
The current system
works fine,

311
00:11:35,899 --> 00:11:36,865
and I don't appreciate
you speaking to Harvey

312
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,116
in such
a disrespectful manner.

313
00:11:38,152 --> 00:11:39,701
- Are you shitting me?
- Harvey, I'm sorry.

314
00:11:39,737 --> 00:11:42,070
Save your sorries, Louis.
This meeting's over.

315
00:11:42,122 --> 00:11:43,455
Harvey, listen.
I'm on your side.

316
00:11:43,490 --> 00:11:45,050
Yeah. I don't need you
on my side, okay?

317
00:11:45,075 --> 00:11:46,375
- I have shit to do.
- Wait.

318
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:47,376
I haven't even brought up
my proposal yet

319
00:11:47,411 --> 00:11:48,527
for the men's bathroom.

320
00:11:48,562 --> 00:11:50,328
You want to finish
being king for a day?

321
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:51,413
Be my guest.

322
00:11:51,465 --> 00:11:53,665
Enjoy your coffee
and your 50 sugars,

323
00:11:53,717 --> 00:11:56,551
and go for it, but like I said,
I have shit to do.

324
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:06,144
Stanley was a good man.

325
00:12:06,180 --> 00:12:08,063
Never missed a day of work,

326
00:12:08,098 --> 00:12:10,098
provided for his family.

327
00:12:11,602 --> 00:12:13,602
He didn't deserve
what happened to him.

328
00:12:15,572 --> 00:12:16,855
What did happen?

329
00:12:16,907 --> 00:12:18,256
Like I told
the other lawyer,

330
00:12:18,292 --> 00:12:21,443
he went to the hospital
with chest pains.

331
00:12:21,495 --> 00:12:23,945
They said it was nothing.

332
00:12:23,997 --> 00:12:25,697
He kept complaining.

333
00:12:25,749 --> 00:12:28,266
Stanley never complained.

334
00:12:28,302 --> 00:12:31,336
Two days later
they released him.

335
00:12:31,371 --> 00:12:34,306
Stanley went to sleep
in our bed that night.

336
00:12:34,341 --> 00:12:37,259
And he never woke up.

337
00:12:37,294 --> 00:12:39,211
No.

338
00:12:39,213 --> 00:12:40,879
He didn't.

339
00:12:40,931 --> 00:12:42,764
Are you sure the hospital
released him

340
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,966
because the insurance company
cut his stay?

341
00:12:45,018 --> 00:12:47,352
He was sick, Mr. Ross,

342
00:12:47,387 --> 00:12:49,638
and they just sent him home.

343
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:51,857
There are over 200
other people

344
00:12:51,892 --> 00:12:54,893
who had the exact same thing
happen to them.

345
00:12:54,895 --> 00:12:56,394
You think
that's a coincidence?

346
00:12:56,396 --> 00:12:58,113
No, I don't,

347
00:12:58,148 --> 00:13:00,482
which is why I'm considering
reopening this case.

348
00:13:00,534 --> 00:13:03,068
So what's stopping you?

349
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,319
Well, for one thing,
I want to know

350
00:13:04,371 --> 00:13:05,704
why your other lawyer
dropped out.

351
00:13:05,739 --> 00:13:07,906
Because they worked that man
to the bone.

352
00:13:07,908 --> 00:13:10,242
He almost lost
his entire practice,

353
00:13:10,294 --> 00:13:13,745
but I was told that you're
with a big, powerful firm.

354
00:13:13,747 --> 00:13:16,631
I am...

355
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:18,083
but I don't know
if I'm gonna be able

356
00:13:18,085 --> 00:13:19,801
to get them
to sign off on this.

357
00:13:19,837 --> 00:13:22,804
So what are we
supposed to do?

358
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,756
You're supposed
to sit tight.

359
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,344
- What the hell was that?
- What are you talking about?

360
00:13:29,396 --> 00:13:30,929
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

361
00:13:30,931 --> 00:13:31,980
You stormed out
of the meeting

362
00:13:32,015 --> 00:13:33,098
that we were supposed
to run together.

363
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,900
I didn't storm out,
I walked out

364
00:13:34,935 --> 00:13:37,018
because you were doing
a shitty job running it.

365
00:13:37,070 --> 00:13:38,353
What are you talking about?
I had your back.

366
00:13:38,405 --> 00:13:40,605
After you let that clown
come after my salary.

367
00:13:40,657 --> 00:13:41,857
I didn't let him
do anything.

368
00:13:41,909 --> 00:13:44,326
I defended you,
and then you smack me down,

369
00:13:44,361 --> 00:13:46,161
after which I had
to postpone a presentation

370
00:13:46,196 --> 00:13:47,579
that I was
very passionate about.

371
00:13:47,614 --> 00:13:50,582
It's a bathroom, Louis.
It smells sometimes.

372
00:13:50,617 --> 00:13:51,937
So why don't you
just go in there,

373
00:13:51,952 --> 00:13:53,702
do what people do in there,
and get out of my face?

374
00:13:53,754 --> 00:13:55,370
You know what?
Donna was right.

375
00:13:55,422 --> 00:13:57,839
I should have never tried
to make things right with you.

376
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:00,091
- Make things right with me?
- Yeah, Harvey.

377
00:14:00,127 --> 00:14:03,011
I let Jack do that so that
I could put him in his place

378
00:14:03,046 --> 00:14:05,463
and show you that I had
your back, but you can't see it

379
00:14:05,465 --> 00:14:07,799
because you're too damn jealous
of me and Donna.

380
00:14:07,801 --> 00:14:09,935
- What did you just say to me?
- You're jealous.

381
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:12,470
You know what, Louis,

382
00:14:12,523 --> 00:14:14,689
if I was so upset
about the two of you,

383
00:14:14,725 --> 00:14:16,641
why am I still paying
her salary?

384
00:14:16,693 --> 00:14:18,310
Bullshit.
The firm pays her salary.

385
00:14:18,312 --> 00:14:19,728
Not all of it.

386
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:22,147
You see, when I brought her
over here from the DA's office,

387
00:14:22,149 --> 00:14:24,282
Jessica wouldn't hire her
because I was an associate,

388
00:14:24,318 --> 00:14:26,034
so I paid her salary.

389
00:14:26,069 --> 00:14:27,319
And then I made partner,

390
00:14:27,371 --> 00:14:29,821
and I didn't think it
was enough, so I paid her more.

391
00:14:29,823 --> 00:14:33,158
And again and again
and again.

392
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,410
So I've had enough
of you telling me I'm jealous.

393
00:14:35,462 --> 00:14:37,078
Yeah, well, Donna
doesn't work for you anymore.

394
00:14:37,130 --> 00:14:38,380
She works for me,
and the only person

395
00:14:38,415 --> 00:14:40,549
who's gonna be taking care
of her salary--this guy.

396
00:14:40,584 --> 00:14:42,000
- You got that?
- Fine by me.

397
00:14:42,052 --> 00:14:43,585
But before you say that,

398
00:14:43,637 --> 00:14:45,420
you better know what you're
getting yourself into.

399
00:14:45,472 --> 00:14:47,138
Oh, yeah, I know what
I'm getting myself into,

400
00:14:47,174 --> 00:14:49,891
because you can't put a price
tag on a woman like that.

401
00:14:57,082 --> 00:14:58,132
I need to talk to you.

402
00:14:58,168 --> 00:14:59,300
Let me guess.

403
00:14:59,336 --> 00:15:01,169
You got into a pissing contest
with Harvey,

404
00:15:01,221 --> 00:15:03,504
he told you he's been
covering Donna's salary,

405
00:15:03,556 --> 00:15:05,840
you, out of pride, said that
you were going to take it on,

406
00:15:05,892 --> 00:15:07,425
and now you're here to find out
how much you're on the hook for.

407
00:15:07,477 --> 00:15:08,760
- Nothing like that.
- Oh, good.

408
00:15:08,762 --> 00:15:10,094
- Then what is it?
- Everything you just said.

409
00:15:10,096 --> 00:15:11,262
- Louis--
- Jessica, please.

410
00:15:11,264 --> 00:15:12,647
- I just want to see the number.
- Okay, Louis.

411
00:15:12,682 --> 00:15:13,865
You want to see the number?
Here's the number.

412
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:16,684
Thank y--
holy goddamn shit.

413
00:15:16,736 --> 00:15:18,186
Are you sure you didn't
accidentally add a zero?

414
00:15:18,238 --> 00:15:20,238
Yes, I'm sure.

415
00:15:21,241 --> 00:15:22,357
Is there any way
the firm can--

416
00:15:22,409 --> 00:15:24,192
The firm is not going
to pick this up.

417
00:15:24,244 --> 00:15:26,494
Harvey knew that, and he chose
to pay her more anyway.

418
00:15:26,529 --> 00:15:27,662
What the hell
am I supposed to do?

419
00:15:27,697 --> 00:15:29,163
Well, it seems to me
you have two options:

420
00:15:29,199 --> 00:15:31,559
You can tell Donna that Harvey's
been augmenting her salary,

421
00:15:31,584 --> 00:15:32,700
and you don't want
to do it anymore.

422
00:15:32,752 --> 00:15:34,836
- Negatory.
- Or you can pay it yourself.

423
00:15:34,871 --> 00:15:36,587
- Not happening.
- There is a third option.

424
00:15:36,623 --> 00:15:38,706
I can send her
back to Harvey.

425
00:15:38,758 --> 00:15:40,758
How dare you?

426
00:15:49,552 --> 00:15:51,386
What do you mean I'm not liquid?

427
00:15:51,438 --> 00:15:55,690
Who told you
to only save 10% cash?

428
00:15:55,725 --> 00:15:57,308
Well,
I don't care what I said.

429
00:15:57,310 --> 00:15:58,476
Does my podiatrist
listen to me

430
00:15:58,478 --> 00:16:00,695
when I tell him
I have hammertoe?

431
00:16:01,865 --> 00:16:02,864
Is everything okay, Louis?

432
00:16:02,899 --> 00:16:05,149
- Everything's wonderful.
- Okay.

433
00:16:05,201 --> 00:16:07,452
Actually, it occurred to me

434
00:16:07,487 --> 00:16:10,872
that we have not discussed
a very important subject.

435
00:16:10,907 --> 00:16:12,957
What is it?

436
00:16:12,992 --> 00:16:15,960
Donna, money's
a very sensitive issue.

437
00:16:15,995 --> 00:16:17,161
Mm-hmm.

438
00:16:17,163 --> 00:16:18,663
And I think you should be
fairly compensated.

439
00:16:18,715 --> 00:16:21,716
I mean, I know how hard it was
for you to leave Harvey for me,

440
00:16:21,751 --> 00:16:23,334
and I am forever grateful.

441
00:16:23,336 --> 00:16:25,336
- It's just that I--
- Louis, shh.

442
00:16:25,338 --> 00:16:27,672
I don't need a huge raise.

443
00:16:27,674 --> 00:16:30,224
The standard 2%
is more than enough.

444
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:32,844
- 2%?
- Yes.

445
00:16:32,846 --> 00:16:34,345
You have a huge heart,

446
00:16:34,347 --> 00:16:36,931
but I already make more
than every other secretary

447
00:16:36,983 --> 00:16:38,182
at the firm, so--

448
00:16:38,184 --> 00:16:40,685
- 2% it is.
- Thanks, Louis.

449
00:16:40,737 --> 00:16:42,737
Don't mention it.

450
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,866
Hey, do you have a second?

451
00:16:54,918 --> 00:16:56,567
I need your legal advice
about something.

452
00:16:56,603 --> 00:16:58,836
Yeah, of course.
What is it?

453
00:16:58,872 --> 00:17:01,372
My fiancée left this prenup
in the kitchen.

454
00:17:01,374 --> 00:17:04,275
I'm just wondering
if you think I should sign it.

455
00:17:06,846 --> 00:17:08,379
Mike, it's not
what it looks like.

456
00:17:08,381 --> 00:17:10,298
It looks like your father
had a prenup prepared

457
00:17:10,350 --> 00:17:11,716
for you to make me sign.

458
00:17:11,768 --> 00:17:13,217
Then it's exactly
what it looks like.

459
00:17:13,269 --> 00:17:14,852
And I'm guessing
you don't want me to sign it?

460
00:17:14,888 --> 00:17:16,220
No, I don't,

461
00:17:16,272 --> 00:17:18,222
because he's been trying
to control me my entire life,

462
00:17:18,224 --> 00:17:19,891
and I'm not gonna
let him do that with this.

463
00:17:19,943 --> 00:17:21,659
Has it occurred to you

464
00:17:21,694 --> 00:17:24,228
that maybe your father is only
doing this because he loves you?

465
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:25,730
I don't really care
why he's doing it.

466
00:17:25,782 --> 00:17:27,865
Great marriages
don't start with contracts.

467
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:29,567
- I know that.
- Then why are you grilling me?

468
00:17:29,619 --> 00:17:31,235
Hey.

469
00:17:31,237 --> 00:17:33,538
Because there's a reason that
you didn't tell me about this,

470
00:17:33,573 --> 00:17:36,741
and I need to know
what it is.

471
00:17:36,743 --> 00:17:39,243
My dad said
he doesn't know the man

472
00:17:39,245 --> 00:17:43,297
that I'm choosing to marry,

473
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:46,167
and I just--

474
00:17:46,219 --> 00:17:49,320
I didn't want
to tell you that.

475
00:17:49,355 --> 00:17:53,140
- Well, I found out anyway.
- Yeah.

476
00:17:53,176 --> 00:17:56,594
Rachel, in the future,

477
00:17:56,646 --> 00:17:58,312
I want you to feel comfortable
telling me this stuff

478
00:17:58,348 --> 00:18:00,765
in the first place.

479
00:18:00,817 --> 00:18:02,600
I will.

480
00:18:10,944 --> 00:18:12,527
Mr. Specter, I wanted to--

481
00:18:12,579 --> 00:18:13,778
You're still here?

482
00:18:13,830 --> 00:18:15,329
I don't leave
until you leave.

483
00:18:15,365 --> 00:18:17,031
Well, in that case, what time
is my meeting with Adidas?

484
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:18,165
11:15.

485
00:18:18,201 --> 00:18:20,585
I moved your 11:00 to 3:00
and your 3:00 to 5:00.

486
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:21,586
- Did you line up--
- Buyers?

487
00:18:21,621 --> 00:18:23,454
I did
but not for another week.

488
00:18:23,456 --> 00:18:25,039
Nike and Puma are overseas,
and you said

489
00:18:25,091 --> 00:18:26,707
Reebok didn't matter
if the other two can't be there.

490
00:18:26,759 --> 00:18:28,209
God damn it.

491
00:18:28,261 --> 00:18:30,127
- There's one more thing.
- What difference does it make?

492
00:18:30,179 --> 00:18:31,963
I can't delay the sale
if I don't know

493
00:18:32,015 --> 00:18:33,855
why my client is dumping
his company on a whim.

494
00:18:33,883 --> 00:18:35,683
That's the one more thing.

495
00:18:35,718 --> 00:18:37,268
Mr. Doyle's best friend died

496
00:18:37,303 --> 00:18:38,936
a month ago
of pancreatic cancer.

497
00:18:38,972 --> 00:18:40,354
He was 46.

498
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:41,606
How'd you know that?

499
00:18:41,641 --> 00:18:43,524
Something he said to you
just before he started

500
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:45,526
talking shit about me
stuck in my head.

501
00:18:45,562 --> 00:18:47,144
What exactly was that?

502
00:18:47,146 --> 00:18:49,814
When people say "life is short"
two times in 30 seconds,

503
00:18:49,866 --> 00:18:51,983
it's usually right
after somebody died.

504
00:18:51,985 --> 00:18:53,734
I take it you were listening
to our conversation.

505
00:18:53,786 --> 00:18:55,903
That's what
good secretaries do.

506
00:18:55,955 --> 00:18:58,289
- Sorry about the Keebler thing.
- You didn't say it.

507
00:18:58,324 --> 00:19:00,491
Besides, it doesn't take
Albert Einstein to figure out

508
00:19:00,543 --> 00:19:02,326
why you hired somebody
that look like me

509
00:19:02,378 --> 00:19:03,961
to replace somebody
that look like her.

510
00:19:03,997 --> 00:19:05,079
Listen, Gretchen, I--

511
00:19:05,131 --> 00:19:07,298
You don't have to worry
about that with me.

512
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:09,333
I prefer my men manly.

513
00:19:11,337 --> 00:19:14,505
Am I not manly?

514
00:19:14,507 --> 00:19:16,507
Well, if you have to ask...

515
00:19:24,183 --> 00:19:26,350
Mike, how you doing?

516
00:19:26,352 --> 00:19:27,568
Robert.

517
00:19:27,604 --> 00:19:28,936
What can I do for you?

518
00:19:28,988 --> 00:19:31,272
I heard you wanted me
to sign a prenup.

519
00:19:31,324 --> 00:19:32,990
I did.

520
00:19:33,026 --> 00:19:34,108
I hope
you didn't take it personally.

521
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,776
Of course not,
I'm happy to sign it,

522
00:19:35,828 --> 00:19:37,194
but Rachel did say
that you don't know

523
00:19:37,246 --> 00:19:40,281
what kind of guy I am,
so I thought I'd come here

524
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:44,835
to show you that this is
the kind of guy I am.

525
00:19:44,871 --> 00:19:46,621
You're going
after Kelton Insurance?

526
00:19:46,673 --> 00:19:48,372
It's not about
who I'm going after.

527
00:19:48,374 --> 00:19:50,174
It's about
who I'm representing.

528
00:19:50,209 --> 00:19:52,176
I'm putting my ass on the line
for 200 people

529
00:19:52,211 --> 00:19:54,011
who have no one to fight
for them other than me,

530
00:19:54,047 --> 00:19:55,796
so if you're worried that
I'd go after Rachel's money

531
00:19:55,848 --> 00:19:57,014
if something went wrong--

532
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,432
You're not
that type of guy.

533
00:19:58,468 --> 00:19:59,934
No, I'm not.

534
00:19:59,969 --> 00:20:01,769
I respect that.

535
00:20:01,804 --> 00:20:02,887
Thank you, sir.

536
00:20:02,939 --> 00:20:05,306
But let me
tell you something.

537
00:20:05,358 --> 00:20:08,309
I used to be one
of those people,

538
00:20:08,361 --> 00:20:11,562
and I scratched and clawed
my way to where I am today,

539
00:20:11,614 --> 00:20:13,147
which is why I know

540
00:20:13,199 --> 00:20:15,116
when you come from nothing
and you make yourself

541
00:20:15,151 --> 00:20:16,817
into something,
you're always waiting

542
00:20:16,869 --> 00:20:18,749
for the day they're gonna
come and take it away.

543
00:20:18,788 --> 00:20:21,372
I'm telling you
that I come from nothing,

544
00:20:21,407 --> 00:20:22,573
and I would never do that.

545
00:20:22,575 --> 00:20:24,375
I'm not saying
you're gonna take it.

546
00:20:24,410 --> 00:20:25,543
I'm saying
you might do something

547
00:20:25,578 --> 00:20:27,244
that makes
someone else take it.

548
00:20:27,246 --> 00:20:28,579
What do you mean?

549
00:20:28,581 --> 00:20:30,081
You're learning at the feet
of Harvey Specter

550
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:31,382
and Jessica Pearson,

551
00:20:31,417 --> 00:20:32,667
and they know
something I know.

552
00:20:32,719 --> 00:20:35,152
You're gonna be
a great lawyer.

553
00:20:35,188 --> 00:20:38,222
You're gonna
crack some eggs,

554
00:20:38,257 --> 00:20:39,924
and you never know
when someone's gonna come at you

555
00:20:39,926 --> 00:20:42,393
to take what's yours
for something you did.

556
00:20:42,428 --> 00:20:44,562
- Robert, I would never--
- Let me finish.

557
00:20:46,599 --> 00:20:49,233
I'm telling you this
because you're gonna be family.

558
00:20:49,268 --> 00:20:53,604
You might not have crossed
any lines yet, but you will.

559
00:20:53,606 --> 00:20:57,324
I'm just trying
to protect my baby girl.

560
00:20:59,529 --> 00:21:01,445
Jessica,
you wanted to see me?

561
00:21:01,497 --> 00:21:03,581
Actually, Louis
wants to see both of us.

562
00:21:03,616 --> 00:21:04,865
Then let's get it over with.

563
00:21:04,917 --> 00:21:06,534
Okay.

564
00:21:06,586 --> 00:21:07,952
I would like to propose

565
00:21:08,004 --> 00:21:09,453
a revamping
of the pay structure

566
00:21:09,455 --> 00:21:11,122
under the following guidelines.

567
00:21:11,174 --> 00:21:13,874
We increase the percentage
of billables the partners get.

568
00:21:13,926 --> 00:21:16,127
We decrease the percentage
of contingent fees

569
00:21:16,129 --> 00:21:17,762
- by an offsetting amount.
- What?

570
00:21:17,797 --> 00:21:18,929
That's what Jack Soloff
said yesterday.

571
00:21:18,965 --> 00:21:20,297
No, this is different.

572
00:21:20,299 --> 00:21:22,600
I've capped the amount
it affects any one partner.

573
00:21:22,635 --> 00:21:23,968
You got to be shitting me.

574
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:25,770
I know you're wondering why
I'm proposing this.

575
00:21:25,805 --> 00:21:27,972
It's crystal clear
why you're proposing it.

576
00:21:28,024 --> 00:21:30,474
You get the exact amount
to cover Donna's salary,

577
00:21:30,526 --> 00:21:31,559
and you take it
out of my paycheck.

578
00:21:31,611 --> 00:21:32,611
Louis--

579
00:21:32,612 --> 00:21:33,561
This has nothing to do
with that.

580
00:21:33,613 --> 00:21:34,613
Jack had a great idea.

581
00:21:34,647 --> 00:21:35,730
It just needed
some fine-tuning.

582
00:21:35,782 --> 00:21:37,348
Fine-tuning?
You're the one that said

583
00:21:37,383 --> 00:21:38,866
you only let him
bring it up

584
00:21:38,901 --> 00:21:40,234
so that you can
smack it down.

585
00:21:40,286 --> 00:21:41,485
Is that true?

586
00:21:41,487 --> 00:21:43,654
Yes. Maybe, but I had
some time to think about it.

587
00:21:43,706 --> 00:21:44,989
Jack put something
on the table,

588
00:21:45,041 --> 00:21:46,457
and it's our duty
to follow through on it.

589
00:21:46,492 --> 00:21:48,492
Oh, bullshit--you're only
following through on it

590
00:21:48,544 --> 00:21:49,960
because you're a cheap
son of a bitch.

591
00:21:49,996 --> 00:21:50,996
Harvey.

592
00:21:50,997 --> 00:21:52,129
I don't want to hear it,
Jessica.

593
00:21:52,165 --> 00:21:53,831
Yesterday, he accused me
of being jealous.

594
00:21:53,883 --> 00:21:55,203
Today, he's coming
after my money.

595
00:21:55,218 --> 00:21:56,467
- No, I'm not--
- Shut up.

596
00:21:56,502 --> 00:21:58,469
We both know Donna
going to work for you

597
00:21:58,504 --> 00:21:59,670
has nothing to do with you.

598
00:21:59,722 --> 00:22:01,138
- You got lucky.
- Lucky?

599
00:22:01,174 --> 00:22:02,923
Like a monkey
who won the lottery,

600
00:22:02,975 --> 00:22:05,509
so the least you can do is
be a man, pay her yourself,

601
00:22:05,511 --> 00:22:07,261
or suck it up
and tell her the truth.

602
00:22:07,313 --> 00:22:08,429
All right. That's enough.
We're not doing this.

603
00:22:08,481 --> 00:22:09,681
- I am a name partner.
- Louis.

604
00:22:09,682 --> 00:22:11,015
No. He has no right to--

605
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:13,517
I will slap the taste
out of your mouth.

606
00:22:19,325 --> 00:22:20,407
Thanks, Jessica.

607
00:22:20,443 --> 00:22:22,026
I appreciate you being
on the same page.

608
00:22:22,028 --> 00:22:23,027
Oh, we're not
on the same page.

609
00:22:23,079 --> 00:22:24,411
What are you talking about?

610
00:22:24,447 --> 00:22:25,863
I wanted the two of you
to run that meeting yesterday

611
00:22:25,865 --> 00:22:28,065
to see if you were okay
with each other, but you're not.

612
00:22:28,084 --> 00:22:30,668
He may be cheap,
but he's right.

613
00:22:30,703 --> 00:22:32,419
You are taking your
Donna anger out on him,

614
00:22:32,455 --> 00:22:33,871
and it needs to stop.

615
00:22:33,923 --> 00:22:34,923
I don't have Donna anger.

616
00:22:34,924 --> 00:22:36,540
Oh, like hell you don't.

617
00:22:36,592 --> 00:22:38,342
And if you don't admit that
to yourself,

618
00:22:38,377 --> 00:22:40,795
I'll slap the taste
out of your mouth too.

619
00:22:49,765 --> 00:22:52,734
What you working on there,
Mike?

620
00:22:52,769 --> 00:22:56,771
Um, nothing.
Just some cleanup.

621
00:22:56,823 --> 00:22:58,023
What can I do
for you, Jessica?

622
00:22:58,075 --> 00:23:00,241
You can tell me why
you reopened a case

623
00:23:00,277 --> 00:23:01,609
against a major
insurance company

624
00:23:01,661 --> 00:23:04,779
we were never a part of
to start with.

625
00:23:04,781 --> 00:23:06,448
Um, I reopened it

626
00:23:06,450 --> 00:23:08,583
because I looked at it
and it's a winner.

627
00:23:08,618 --> 00:23:09,784
Well, I also looked at it,

628
00:23:09,786 --> 00:23:12,203
and I say it's a loser.

629
00:23:12,255 --> 00:23:13,255
Jessica, look--

630
00:23:13,256 --> 00:23:14,422
You took a case
on contingency

631
00:23:14,458 --> 00:23:17,125
where every plaintiff
is dirt poor,

632
00:23:17,177 --> 00:23:18,676
which means, even if we win,

633
00:23:18,712 --> 00:23:20,628
compensation for lost wages
is nothing.

634
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:21,963
You're leaving out
punitive damages,

635
00:23:22,015 --> 00:23:24,215
and Harvey takes cases
on contingency all the time.

636
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:25,884
Yeah, he takes them
to make money,

637
00:23:25,936 --> 00:23:27,302
not to save kittens
in trees.

638
00:23:27,354 --> 00:23:29,471
And I just told you
this is going to make money.

639
00:23:29,473 --> 00:23:31,056
And that's what you said
about Liberty Rail,

640
00:23:31,108 --> 00:23:32,273
and instead of making money,

641
00:23:32,309 --> 00:23:34,242
it almost ended
with Donna behind bars.

642
00:23:34,277 --> 00:23:36,144
No one is going to jail
for this.

643
00:23:36,196 --> 00:23:38,863
No, they're not, because it's
going to cost a fortune to fund,

644
00:23:38,899 --> 00:23:41,449
and I'm not laying out that kind
of money on a long shot.

645
00:23:41,485 --> 00:23:43,318
Jessica, look.
I promised myself that I--

646
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:45,036
I don't care
who you promised.

647
00:23:45,072 --> 00:23:47,155
You took this case
without running it by me,

648
00:23:47,157 --> 00:23:49,290
and you did it
because you knew I'd say no.

649
00:23:49,326 --> 00:23:50,959
- Jessica--
- So that's enough.

650
00:23:50,994 --> 00:23:53,995
Dump it, or I will.

651
00:24:02,589 --> 00:24:04,506
I need to talk to you.

652
00:24:04,558 --> 00:24:05,840
Really?

653
00:24:05,892 --> 00:24:07,092
'Cause the last time
you talked to me,

654
00:24:07,144 --> 00:24:09,427
you told me to open my mouth,
and you slammed it shut.

655
00:24:09,479 --> 00:24:11,896
Because you wanted to go after
Harvey, but now I'm on board.

656
00:24:11,932 --> 00:24:14,399
- Why should I believe you?
- Answer me this.

657
00:24:14,434 --> 00:24:16,067
How many partners
do you have in your pocket,

658
00:24:16,103 --> 00:24:17,735
if we put your proposal
to a vote?

659
00:24:17,771 --> 00:24:19,104
I can get 45%.

660
00:24:19,156 --> 00:24:20,355
Well, then the reason
you can believe me

661
00:24:20,357 --> 00:24:21,606
is that I'm gonna get you
the difference.

662
00:24:21,658 --> 00:24:23,691
How you gonna do that
if you don't have the courage

663
00:24:23,693 --> 00:24:25,410
to back my plan
at your own meeting?

664
00:24:25,445 --> 00:24:27,495
By showing everyone
at this firm exactly

665
00:24:27,531 --> 00:24:28,780
what Harvey makes.

666
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:32,117
Now I know
you're bullshitting me.

667
00:24:32,169 --> 00:24:34,169
You'd be fired
if you did that.

668
00:24:34,204 --> 00:24:35,920
Not if I do it by accident.

669
00:24:40,627 --> 00:24:42,293
Can you believe
that sneaker brings in

670
00:24:42,345 --> 00:24:44,379
over a billion dollars
from China alone?

671
00:24:44,381 --> 00:24:46,047
With earnings like that,
makes me wonder

672
00:24:46,099 --> 00:24:48,433
why you're trying
to rip off my client.

673
00:24:48,468 --> 00:24:50,135
Buying a man's company
for a fair price

674
00:24:50,187 --> 00:24:51,769
is hardly ripping him off.

675
00:24:51,805 --> 00:24:53,521
But it's not a fair price.

676
00:24:53,557 --> 00:24:56,274
You gave my client 48 hours
to take your offer.

677
00:24:56,309 --> 00:24:58,443
I'm gonna give you five minutes
to take mine.

678
00:24:58,478 --> 00:25:00,278
Double your money,
or I walk out the door.

679
00:25:00,313 --> 00:25:01,396
That's ridiculous.

680
00:25:01,398 --> 00:25:03,148
What's ridiculous
is you preying on a man

681
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,066
who just lost
his lifelong friend.

682
00:25:05,068 --> 00:25:07,202
I'm a businessman,
not a grief counselor.

683
00:25:07,237 --> 00:25:08,620
Then let me counsel you
on this.

684
00:25:08,655 --> 00:25:10,488
Because he's grieving,
I have the ability

685
00:25:10,540 --> 00:25:12,060
to go to the board
and delay this sale.

686
00:25:12,075 --> 00:25:13,625
But you're not going to,
because you know

687
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:15,493
it'll drive down
the price even more

688
00:25:15,545 --> 00:25:17,912
when he eventually
wants to sell anyway.

689
00:25:17,914 --> 00:25:20,081
You're right,
it will,

690
00:25:20,133 --> 00:25:21,883
but I'll tell you what,
Mr. Polk,

691
00:25:21,918 --> 00:25:23,918
it'll still be worth
more than your offer.

692
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:26,554
And after my client's grief
passes,

693
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:28,640
he may still want to sell,

694
00:25:28,675 --> 00:25:30,175
but it sure as hell
won't be to you.

695
00:25:30,227 --> 00:25:38,227
♪ ♪

696
00:25:54,618 --> 00:25:56,784
I got to call you back.

697
00:25:56,786 --> 00:25:58,786
How the hell
did you get in here?

698
00:25:58,838 --> 00:26:01,756
I fired your assistant
ten minutes after I fired you.

699
00:26:01,791 --> 00:26:03,291
Guess Amy still knows
how to get a person through.

700
00:26:03,293 --> 00:26:04,542
Congratulations.

701
00:26:04,594 --> 00:26:06,127
You made your way in.
You can make your way out.

702
00:26:06,179 --> 00:26:08,546
Not before I give you
the chance to make $20 million.

703
00:26:15,055 --> 00:26:16,304
Mm-hmm. What makes you think
I want to get in the business

704
00:26:16,356 --> 00:26:17,939
of underwriting
class-action lawsuits?

705
00:26:17,974 --> 00:26:19,814
Because you're in the business
of making money,

706
00:26:19,859 --> 00:26:21,476
and before you say no,

707
00:26:21,528 --> 00:26:23,144
I'm gonna give you
20% off the top.

708
00:26:23,146 --> 00:26:24,312
It's the best deal
out there.

709
00:26:24,364 --> 00:26:27,949
Well, that's not
good enough.

710
00:26:27,984 --> 00:26:31,319
25%.

711
00:26:31,371 --> 00:26:33,988
Are you authorized
to do that?

712
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,957
No, you're not.

713
00:26:35,992 --> 00:26:38,312
Knowing you, you probably don't
even have the authorization

714
00:26:38,328 --> 00:26:39,661
to come to me
in the first place.

715
00:26:39,713 --> 00:26:41,713
I came to you because this is
our chance to make it right.

716
00:26:41,748 --> 00:26:43,998
Bullshit.
You need money.

717
00:26:44,050 --> 00:26:45,917
That's the only reason you're
standing here in front of me.

718
00:26:45,969 --> 00:26:48,503
Jonathan,
I could have gone anywhere.

719
00:26:48,505 --> 00:26:50,972
I came to you for the same
reason I went to Walter Gillis,

720
00:26:51,007 --> 00:26:52,090
to make it right.

721
00:26:52,142 --> 00:26:53,725
Pick up the phone
and ask him.

722
00:26:58,815 --> 00:27:01,816
I'm not Walter Gillis.

723
00:27:01,851 --> 00:27:05,520
Tell Amy I said "thank you"
for getting you past security,

724
00:27:05,572 --> 00:27:08,022
'cause now I'm gonna call
every investment banker I know

725
00:27:08,024 --> 00:27:10,024
and tell them to pass
on your offer

726
00:27:10,076 --> 00:27:12,360
because Mike Ross
can't be trusted.

727
00:27:23,757 --> 00:27:24,956
What the hell is this?

728
00:27:25,008 --> 00:27:26,374
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

729
00:27:26,376 --> 00:27:28,843
Yes, you do. This is Harvey's
last three income statements,

730
00:27:28,878 --> 00:27:30,795
and I found them sitting
in the copy machine.

731
00:27:30,847 --> 00:27:32,130
Donna, I need you to put that
back where you found it,

732
00:27:32,182 --> 00:27:34,215
and I need you
to put it back now.

733
00:27:34,217 --> 00:27:35,967
- I won't do it.
- That was not a request.

734
00:27:36,019 --> 00:27:37,051
- That was an order.
- I don't care.

735
00:27:37,103 --> 00:27:38,936
- I'm not gonna let you do this.
- See?

736
00:27:38,972 --> 00:27:40,855
I knew that you would jump
at the first opportunity

737
00:27:40,890 --> 00:27:42,390
you had to take his side
over mine.

738
00:27:42,392 --> 00:27:44,225
This isn't me
taking Harvey's side.

739
00:27:44,227 --> 00:27:47,395
This is me stopping you
from making a huge mistake.

740
00:27:47,397 --> 00:27:49,530
And if he did the same thing,
you wouldn't be stopping him.

741
00:27:49,566 --> 00:27:51,449
Harvey would never
do anything like this,

742
00:27:51,484 --> 00:27:53,067
and if he did,
I sure as hell would.

743
00:27:53,119 --> 00:27:54,569
- Oh, bullshit.
- No, Louis.

744
00:27:54,621 --> 00:27:55,737
